### **Standing Rock 2020 Court Win: The Big Details (Plain English)**

The **2020 court win** was a **huge victory** for the Standing Rock Sioux Tribe against the **Dakota Access Pipeline (DAPL)**. On **March 25, 2020**, a federal judge in Washington, D.C. ruled that the U.S. government **broke environmental laws** when it approved the pipeline. This forced a **new, full study** of risks — the second time the government got called out on this project.<grok:render card_id="98d36a" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
